---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Google Ads Preview Tool – See Your Responsive Search Ads Before Launch"
  description="Preview your Google Ads before publishing. See how headlines and descriptions appear in search results. Free PPC preview tool."
  currentPath="/google-ads-preview-tool"
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>Google Ads Preview Tool</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Preview responsive search ads with your headlines, descriptions, and display URL before launching your campaign.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="card tool-card">
    <div class="preview-grid">
      <div class="inputs-panel">
        <h2>Ad Inputs</h2>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="finalUrl">Final URL</label>
          <input id="finalUrl" type="text" placeholder="https://www.example.com" />
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="path1">Path 1</label>
          <input id="path1" type="text" placeholder="pricing" />
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="path2">Path 2</label>
          <input id="path2" type="text" placeholder="plans" />
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="headline1">Headline 1</label>
          <input id="headline1" type="text" placeholder="Google Ads Management" />
          <p class="input-meta"><span id="headline1Count">0</span> / 30</p>
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="headline2">Headline 2</label>
          <input id="headline2" type="text" placeholder="Free PPC Audit" />
          <p class="input-meta"><span id="headline2Count">0</span> / 30</p>
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="headline3">Headline 3</label>
          <input id="headline3" type="text" placeholder="Trusted by Marketers" />
          <p class="input-meta"><span id="headline3Count">0</span> / 30</p>
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="description1">Description 1</label>
          <textarea id="description1" rows="3" placeholder="Improve campaign performance with practical PPC workflows and better tracking."></textarea>
          <p class="input-meta"><span id="description1Count">0</span> / 90</p>
        </div>

        <div class="field">
          <label for="description2">Description 2</label>
          <textarea id="description2" rows="3" placeholder="Preview your ad copy, validate key limits, and launch with more confidence."></textarea>
          <p class="input-meta"><span id="description2Count">0</span> / 90</p>
        </div>

        <div class="button-row">
          <button class="btn-primary" id="loadExampleBtn" type="button">Load Example</button>
          <button class="btn-secondary" id="resetBtn" type="button">Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="preview-panel">
        <h2>Live Preview</h2>

        <div class="google-preview">
          <div class="preview-url" id="previewUrl">www.example.com › pricing › plans</div>
          <div class="preview-headline" id="previewHeadline">
            Google Ads Management | Free PPC Audit | Trusted by Marketers
          </div>
          <div class="preview-description" id="previewDescription">
            Improve campaign performance with practical PPC workflows and better tracking.
            Preview your ad copy, validate key limits, and launch with more confidence.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="preview-note">
          This preview is an approximation for planning and review purposes. Actual Google Ads rendering may vary by device, auction context, and available space.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card content-card">
    <h2>What This Tool Does</h2>
    <p>
      This Google Ads Preview Tool helps you visualize how your responsive search ad may appear
      in Google search results. You can enter headlines, descriptions, and display paths to create
      a cleaner pre-launch review workflow.
    </p>

    <h2>Why It Helps</h2>
    <p>
      Before launching a campaign, it helps to review how your ad copy looks as a whole — not just
      line by line. Previewing your ad can make it easier to spot awkward combinations, weak value
      propositions, and headline clutter.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Use It</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Enter your final URL and optional display paths.</li>
      <li>Add up to three headline lines for preview.</li>
      <li>Add one or two descriptions.</li>
      <li>Review the live preview card on the right side.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Related Tools</h2>
<p>
  Use our <a href="/google-ads-character-counter">Google Ads Character Counter</a>
  to validate copy length, try the
  <a href="/google-ads-headline-generator">Google Ads Headline Generator</a>
  for new ideas, generate body copy with the
  <a href="/google-ads-description-generator">Google Ads Description Generator</a>,
  or build tracking links with the
  <a href="/utm-builder">UTM Builder</a>.
</p>
  </section>

<section class="card content-card">
  <h2>How to Use the Google Ads Preview Tool Effectively</h2>
  <p>
    To get the most value from this tool, focus on how your headlines and descriptions work together
    as a complete message. Strong Google Ads performance often comes from clarity, relevance, and
    structure rather than just keywords alone.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Keep headlines clear and benefit-driven</li>
    <li>Avoid repeating the same message across multiple headlines</li>
    <li>Make sure descriptions support your main value proposition</li>
    <li>Use the preview to catch awkward phrasing or truncation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Best Practices for Google Ads Preview and Optimization</h2>
  <p>
    Previewing your ads before launching is an important part of campaign optimization. Even small
    improvements in wording can lead to higher click-through rates and better engagement.
  </p>

  <p>
    This preview tool helps you simulate how your ad might appear in search results, allowing you
    to refine your messaging before spending budget on live traffic.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Test multiple headline combinations</li>
    <li>Check readability on different line lengths</li>
    <li>Ensure your call-to-action is clear</li>
    <li>Improve overall ad consistency</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>What is a Google Ads preview tool?</h3>
  <p>
    A Google Ads preview tool allows advertisers to simulate how their ads may appear in search
    results without running a live campaign.
  </p>

  <h3>Does previewing ads affect impressions or performance?</h3>
  <p>
    No. This tool is for planning and testing only and does not generate impressions or affect your
    campaign metrics.
  </p>

  <h3>Why should I preview my ads before launching?</h3>
  <p>
    Previewing helps you improve clarity, avoid formatting issues, and create more effective ad
    copy before spending on clicks.
  </p>
</section>

  <script>
    const finalUrl = document.getElementById("finalUrl");
    const path1 = document.getElementById("path1");
    const path2 = document.getElementById("path2");

    const headline1 = document.getElementById("headline1");
    const headline2 = document.getElementById("headline2");
    const headline3 = document.getElementById("headline3");

    const description1 = document.getElementById("description1");
    const description2 = document.getElementById("description2");

    const previewUrl = document.getElementById("previewUrl");
    const previewHeadline = document.getElementById("previewHeadline");
    const previewDescription = document.getElementById("previewDescription");

    const headline1Count = document.getElementById("headline1Count");
    const headline2Count = document.getElementById("headline2Count");
    const headline3Count = document.getElementById("headline3Count");
    const description1Count = document.getElementById("description1Count");
    const description2Count = document.getElementById("description2Count");

    const loadExampleBtn = document.getElementById("loadExampleBtn");
    const resetBtn = document.getElementById("resetBtn");

    function safeTrim(value) {
      return value.trim();
    }

    function shorten(text, limit) {
      return text.length > limit ? text.slice(0, limit) : text;
    }

    function getDisplayDomain(url) {
      const clean = safeTrim(url);
      if (!clean) return "www.example.com";

      try {
        const parsed = new URL(clean);
        return parsed.hostname.replace(/^www\./, "www.");
      } catch {
        return clean.replace(/^https?:\/\//, "").replace(/\/.*$/, "") || "www.example.com";
      }
    }

    function updateCounts() {
      headline1Count.textContent = headline1.value.length;
      headline2Count.textContent = headline2.value.length;
      headline3Count.textContent = headline3.value.length;
      description1Count.textContent = description1.value.length;
      description2Count.textContent = description2.value.length;
    }

    function updatePreview() {
      updateCounts();

      const domain = getDisplayDomain(finalUrl.value);
      const p1 = safeTrim(path1.value);
      const p2 = safeTrim(path2.value);

      let displayUrl = domain;
      if (p1) displayUrl += ` › ${shorten(p1, 15)}`;
      if (p2) displayUrl += ` › ${shorten(p2, 15)}`;

      previewUrl.textContent = displayUrl;

      const h1 = safeTrim(headline1.value) || "Google Ads Management";
      const h2 = safeTrim(headline2.value) || "Free PPC Audit";
      const h3 = safeTrim(headline3.value) || "Trusted by Marketers";

      previewHeadline.textContent = [
        shorten(h1, 30),
        shorten(h2, 30),
        shorten(h3, 30)
      ].filter(Boolean).join(" | ");

      const d1 = safeTrim(description1.value) || "Improve campaign performance with practical PPC workflows and better tracking.";
      const d2 = safeTrim(description2.value) || "Preview your ad copy, validate key limits, and launch with more confidence.";

      previewDescription.textContent = `${shorten(d1, 90)} ${shorten(d2, 90)}`.trim();
    }

    function loadExample() {
      finalUrl.value = "https://www.ppctoolbench.com";
      path1.value = "google-ads";
      path2.value = "tools";

      headline1.value = "Free PPC Tools";
      headline2.value = "Preview Ads Faster";
      headline3.value = "Built for Marketers";

      description1.value = "Review your responsive search ads before launch with a clean visual preview.";
      description2.value = "Check how headlines and descriptions work together for stronger ad messaging.";

      updatePreview();
    }

    function resetForm() {
      finalUrl.value = "";
      path1.value = "";
      path2.value = "";

      headline1.value = "";
      headline2.value = "";
      headline3.value = "";

      description1.value = "";
      description2.value = "";

      updatePreview();
    }

    [
      finalUrl,
      path1,
      path2,
      headline1,
      headline2,
      headline3,
      description1,
      description2
    ].forEach((el) => {
      el.addEventListener("input", updatePreview);
    });

    loadExampleBtn.addEventListener("click", loadExample);
    resetBtn.addEventListener("click", resetForm);

    updatePreview();
  </script>

  <style>
    .page-header {
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }

    .tool-card,
    .content-card {
      margin-top: 24px;
    }

    .preview-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .field {
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .field:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    label {
      display: block;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 1.02rem;
    }

    input,
    textarea {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-family: inherit;
      background: #fff;
    }

    input:focus,
    textarea:focus {
      outline: 2px solid rgba(109, 40, 217, 0.15);
      border-color: var(--primary);
    }

    textarea {
      resize: vertical;
    }

    .input-meta {
      margin-top: 8px;
      color: #6b7280;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .button-row {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 12px;
    }

    button {
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .btn-primary {
      background: var(--primary);
      color: white;
    }

    .btn-primary:hover {
      background: var(--primary-hover);
    }

    .btn-secondary {
      background: #ede9fe;
      color: #4c1d95;
    }

    .google-preview {
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04);
    }

    .preview-url {
      color: #188038;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    .preview-headline {
      color: #1a0dab;
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      line-height: 1.4;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    .preview-description {
      color: #4b5563;
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      line-height: 1.65;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    .preview-note {
      margin-top: 14px;
      color: #6b7280;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .content-card h2 {
      margin-top: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .content-card h2:first-child {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .content-card p,
    .content-card li {
      color: #374151;
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }

    @media (max-width: 980px) {
      .preview-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>